Modern fungal systematics utilizes molecular markers and a variety of emerging methods which allow proposing new taxa as scientific hypotheses. The course will introduce current developments in delimitation of fungal species and groups at higher taxonomic levels.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to give an overview of fungal systematics including modern classification and methods used in this field.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will know the basics of classification of fungi and have skills in utilizing various phylogenetic methods applied in systematic mycology.
